block content
  div(style="margin-left:350px;margin-right:350px; margin-top:60px; margin-bottom:60px")
    h1(class="text-center") Privacy policy
    p(style="text-align:center; line-height:10px; color:gray; margin-bottom:50px; color:rgb(71, 85, 105);") Last updated on March 1, 2024
    p(class="text-gray-700") Sync-Audio fully respects your right to privacy and utilises the following practices in regards to any information we are provided or obtain about users of this website. Sync-Audio reserves the right at all times to disclose any information as necessary to satisfy any applicable law, regulation, legal process or governmental request, or to edit, refuse to post, or to remove any information or materials, in whole or in part, at our sole discretion.
    h3(class="mt-4") Personally Identifiable Information
    p(class="text-gray-700") In order to use this service, you must where required provide some information such as name and email address. To fulfil licensing transactions or provide other services to you as a customer of Sync-Audio, we may require you to provide certain additional information to us. Because of the nature of the Internet, such data may pass through any country. We use best commercial practices for keeping such data confidential, but there is no guarantee that such practices will prevent the disclosure or further distribution of such data beyond Sync-Audio.
    h3(class="mt-4") Third Party Payment Accounts
    p(class="text-gray-700") Where third parties requiring personal identification information payments including Common items which may include, but are not limited to, your name, address, phone number, and credit card number as may be required by online banking services such as Paypal. By providing this information to PayPal, you are agreeing to allow them to utilise this information to complete all transactions you request through this website and to disclose that information and details of all such transactions to PayPal and any necessary payment processors indemnifies Sync-Audio free from any liabilities resulting from any loss or mishandling of your personal identification information by such third party.
    h3(class="mt-4") Email
    p(class="text-gray-700") Sync-Audio may periodically send promotional emails to its subscribers about services offered by Sync-Audio and its partners. If you provide us with your email address and you do not wish to receive email information from Sync-Audio or its partners, please let us know by emailing us at: info@syncaudio.com We do not pass information about your email addresses to companies who contact us about our marketing statistics.
    h3(class="mt-4") Cookies
    p(class="text-gray-700") When you visit the Sync-Audio website, we place a text file called a "cookie" in the browser directory of your computer's hard drive. A cookie is a small piece of information that a website can store on your web browser and later retrieve. The cookie cannot be read by any website other than the one that set up the cookie. Cookies enable our website to recognise the information you have consented to give to our website, and help us determine what portions of this website are most appropriate for your personal needs. We do NOT use cookies to examine your browsing behaviour before or after leaving the Sync-Audio website. If at any time you believe that Sync-Audio has not followed the above policy, or if you would like your information to be removed from our system, please contact us. We will make reasonable efforts to identify and correct any problem.
    h3(class="mt-4") Google Analytics
    p(class="text-gray-700") When someone visits sync-audio.com we use a third party service, Google Analytics, to collect standard internet log information and details of visitor behaviour patterns. We do this to find out things such as the number of visitors to the various parts of the site. This information is only processed in a way which does not identify anyone. We do not make, and do not allow Google to make, any attempt to find out the identities of those visiting our website.
    h3(class="mt-4") Non-Identifiable Information
    p(class="text-gray-700") This website may give you opportunities to submit non-identifiable information, including but not limited to voting on songs or creating playlists. By submitting this information, you grant Sync-Audio a non-exclusive, irrevocable license to use it in any way, whether aggregated or standalone, that does not use or reveal your personal information. In addition, Sync-Audio reserves the right to use portions of your personal information in an aggregate, non-identifiable way, such as disclosing that there are 1000 registered users from London, UK.
    h3(class="mt-4") Our Promise
    p(class="text-gray-700") We do not share information with members of media and marketing groups and other companies. If we have to send your details to countries without proper data protection laws, we remain responsible for keeping this information secure.
    p(class="text-gray-700") Our Website uses secure socket layer (“SSL”) encryption to protect your personal information whenever it is collected or transmitted. No one can see or edit your personal information without knowing your username and password, so do not share these with anybody.
    h3(class="mt-4") Account Information
    p(class="text-gray-700") When you pay for our service online your credit card details are processed over a secure internet site by our third party payment provider PayPal. When you place a sales order with us using this system. To process your order you will be asked for your name, email address, credit or debit card number and expiry date.
